The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, September 09, 2002 				 Cops held for extortion
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Burdwan, Sept. 8: Local people arrested three policemen from Burdwan police station when they went to collect extortion money from an illicit liquor den at Natunganj. 																								The policemen were kept tied to a lamp post for about two hours till senior officials arrived to rescue them.																								Nityananda Garai, Naba Kumar De and Indison Shah went to Nutanganj to collect the money without knowing that the den was demolished by their colleagues last night.																								Once held by the mob, the policemen confessed that they used to extort money.
